/*--------------------------------*- Choupo -*-----------------------*\
  Component: Sodium chloride (NaCl, CAS 7647-14-5)

  A non-volatile fully-dissociating 1-1 salt --- the canonical solute
  for RO desalination tutorials.  Brackish water is ~5 g/L NaCl;
  seawater is ~35 g/L (~0.6 mol/L NaCl).

  At dilute aqueous concentrations the ideal van't Hoff form
      π = ν R T c        with ν = 2
  predicts the osmotic pressure to within ~5 % up to ~1 mol/L; for
  precise screening at higher concentrations one switches to the
  Pitzer or electrolyte-NRTL activity models (both implemented; selected
  with `activityModel { model pitzer; }` / `{ model eNRTL; }`).  Beyond
  membranes, NaCl now also drives the evaporator (BPE from a_w) and the
  crystalliser (saturation from the ion-activity Ksp) tutorials.

  Properties relevant to membrane simulation:
    MW             58.44 g/mol
    dissociation    2 (fully dissociated 1-1 electrolyte)
    role nonvolatile (never appears in the vapour)

  The vapour-pressure block is left empty: with role nonvolatile
  the runtime never reads it.  Liquid Cp is intentionally absent
  too --- membrane simulations do not run an energy balance on the
  solute side; for tutorials that DO need an energy balance with
  dissolved salt the Cp of the salt-free water dominates by 2-3
  orders of magnitude and the salt contribution is neglected.
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

name           NaCl;
formula        NaCl;
CAS            7647-14-5;

MW             58.44;          // g/mol  (= kg/kmol)
role        nonvolatile;
dissociation   2;              // van't Hoff factor for π = ν R T c

// Salt dissociation map for the electrolyte activity model (pitzer).  cation/anion
// are ion NAMES into data/standards/electrolyte/{ions,pairs}.dat; solubility is the
// measured saturation molality.  Intrinsic salt chemistry, declared ONCE -- a case
// selects `activityModel { model pitzer; }` and re-types nothing.
dissociatesTo  { Na 1; Cl 1; }   // ion stoichiometry (formula-like identity)

// Solid-crystal properties for the population-balance crystalliser (MSMPR/FVM):
// particle density + volume shape factor (V = k_v L^3).  NaCl grows as CUBES.
// PRIMARY: halite density 2.165 g/cm^3 (crystallographic, public domain); k_v = 1.0 (cube).
solid
{
    rho_p   2165.0;     // crystalline NaCl (halite) density [kg/m^3]
    k_v     1.0;        // volume shape factor (cube)
}
